WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:16.640
Welcome.

00:16.640 --> 00:21.200
So this week we're going to be teaching a horse that has never free jumped a little

00:21.200 --> 00:25.240
bit about the game of free jumping.

00:25.240 --> 00:32.840
Some goals that you'll have for today is to make it fun for the horses and have them understand

00:32.840 --> 00:40.440
and experience the exercise in a very attainable way so they don't feel like it's too hard

00:40.440 --> 00:43.280
to accomplish or too complicated.

00:43.280 --> 00:48.400
Some horses thrive in liberty work because they're very independent and other horses

00:48.400 --> 00:52.840
feel that it's a little bit tricky to get started.

00:52.840 --> 00:56.040
So firstly we want to warm the horses up by lunging.

00:56.040 --> 00:58.080
This horse has been warmed up at liberty.

00:58.080 --> 01:05.920
If your horse is not used to or you feel better starting them on a lunge line, that's okay

01:05.920 --> 01:06.920
too.

01:06.920 --> 01:14.120
And then as you can see I'm just walking really cautious and calmly over to the obstacles

01:14.120 --> 01:17.920
and showing her how to step over them.

01:17.920 --> 01:25.560
Our setup has extra jumps and rails as a chute.

01:25.560 --> 01:32.880
You can also use pieces of caution tape or any sort of safe barricade that could come

01:32.880 --> 01:38.920
down in case the horse misunderstands and tries to run out through the chute.

01:38.920 --> 01:44.020
So in this case we've got little wings on either side as well to help guide the horses

01:44.020 --> 01:48.180
into the chute so that they know where to go.

01:48.180 --> 01:54.340
So step one is just to lead them over very small obstacles, just a pile of rails on the

01:54.340 --> 01:56.700
ground.

01:56.700 --> 02:02.700
You can do this with a horse that's done minimal jumping or more jumping as long as you stay

02:02.700 --> 02:08.300
within the boundaries of what they already know how to do or what to do with their bodies.

02:09.300 --> 02:18.020
So as you can see I'm leading her and I'm petting her when she does it correctly.

02:18.020 --> 02:22.260
The next step after you've done this enough times that the horse really gets it is to

02:22.260 --> 02:24.500
allow them to go on their own.

02:24.500 --> 02:29.140
You see how I'm letting her sniff the way that she wants to go over the poles and I'm

02:29.140 --> 02:35.620
just gently staying behind her in somewhat of a lunging position, rewarding her for the

02:35.620 --> 02:39.140
first one.

02:39.140 --> 02:45.300
And then just putting my arm kind of close to her bum as if I'm a little bit lunging

02:45.300 --> 02:54.140
and quietly directing her to go around the poles.

02:54.140 --> 02:59.700
If your horse is very keen or very excited sometimes they'll run off away from you and

02:59.700 --> 03:01.620
that's okay too.

03:01.620 --> 03:06.020
Just be careful that you're not in harm's way if your horse is not very aware of your

03:06.020 --> 03:08.120
surroundings.

03:08.120 --> 03:12.820
This one is very aware of the surroundings.

03:12.820 --> 03:18.700
So you see how she's just walking away, she's taking some liberties, so I'm just engaging

03:18.700 --> 03:26.420
in that lunging kind of posture again with minimal pressure and now I've even been able

03:26.420 --> 03:34.540
to advance to being outside the chute and just talking to her and indicating.

03:34.540 --> 03:38.380
Important thing is to not rush the horses if they still feel the need to walk over the

03:38.380 --> 03:43.980
obstacles, allow them to do that.

03:43.980 --> 03:48.420
So when I squat down like that, that's an indicator of a little break and the horse

03:48.420 --> 03:53.460
is allowed to relax or stay quiet for a moment.

03:53.500 --> 03:59.180
I want to get up again, I'm just going to direct her gently with my body position to

03:59.180 --> 04:03.680
go the way that I intend her to go.

04:03.680 --> 04:08.700
This is very important when the horse walks towards you like that they're asking for help.

04:08.700 --> 04:13.980
So you see me immediately, I'm not pushing from behind anymore, I go straight to her

04:13.980 --> 04:20.680
and I get into a leading position because she clearly got confused of which direction

04:20.680 --> 04:23.140
she should go.

04:23.820 --> 04:32.100
Good, and you see her looking back at me for clarity and then she comes back.

04:32.100 --> 04:39.180
Again this is a very very unique and authentic video, this horse has never free jumped before,

04:39.180 --> 04:42.380
it's never been through a chute.

04:42.380 --> 04:47.980
So this is a very good example of some of your horses if you've never free jumped them

04:47.980 --> 04:48.980
before.

04:49.220 --> 04:54.460
So you see there when she went to go into the chute, I didn't persist or intend for

04:54.460 --> 04:59.220
her to do that so she turned around to come back towards me and that's an acceptable

04:59.220 --> 05:00.980
reaction.

05:00.980 --> 05:05.700
So at no point do you want to be chasing the horses through the chute, they never jump

05:05.700 --> 05:08.900
well like that and they don't have a good understanding.

05:08.900 --> 05:17.980
You want to teach them the exercise and have them go through as they know how and are able.

05:19.900 --> 05:21.820
Much better.

05:21.820 --> 05:27.560
So in this case, aww she's going to the camera man, that's extra cute.

05:27.560 --> 05:33.300
So after some repetitions on the one direction then you can switch sides and even increase

05:33.300 --> 05:41.100
to standing on the end of the chute and letting the horse fully propel its own mind through

05:41.100 --> 05:45.340
the chute, solving all the problems as they go along.

05:45.340 --> 05:51.020
In this particular video you can't hear me saying the praises but I'm indicating with

05:51.020 --> 05:57.060
my voice when to trot and I'm telling her good girl and that is really helping her mood

05:57.060 --> 06:00.980
and her excitement on the subject.

06:00.980 --> 06:05.220
When she's waiting for me like that, that's a very good sign she's understanding the game

06:05.220 --> 06:10.560
and she's starting to know what's expected of her.

06:10.560 --> 06:14.260
So secondly you're going to want to trot in and give them a little momentum, you see me

06:14.380 --> 06:22.580
clapping my hands to encourage her to keep trotting and there she's accepting the reward

06:22.580 --> 06:32.260
and going back to the end of the chute.

06:32.260 --> 06:37.440
Coming and standing next to people is a very good sign for the horses, it's an indication

06:37.440 --> 06:43.240
that they're ready for a reward and you've done a good job with your reward training.

06:43.320 --> 06:47.600
So no matter how the horse goes over the obstacles you're still going to praise them for going

06:47.600 --> 06:50.200
through the chute correctly.

06:50.200 --> 06:54.520
Today we're probably not going to get very far with the jump height and that's a very

06:54.520 --> 06:56.080
good idea.

06:56.080 --> 07:03.360
You want to teach the horse the skills and the set up just the way we teach ourselves.

07:03.360 --> 07:07.240
We want to teach technique first and then go further.

07:07.240 --> 07:12.480
After you get some confidence with cross rails then you can set up a small vertical and just

07:12.480 --> 07:14.860
make sure that the distances are agreeable.

07:14.860 --> 07:20.360
This is a very open two so you can trot in and get a nice three between the two fences

07:20.360 --> 07:26.080
and it's not too awkward for the horses.

07:26.080 --> 07:31.640
Some really important things to remember is to take your time to lower your expectations

07:31.640 --> 07:37.720
for the first few times and just let the horse experience going through the chute correctly.

07:37.720 --> 07:43.360
If you have to keep the rails on the ground for the entire first time, keep leading them,

07:43.360 --> 07:51.720
those things, stay at that exact same spot for a while before moving on to the next stage.

07:51.720 --> 07:56.800
As the horse gets confident they'll start to go on their own or direct themselves to

07:56.800 --> 07:57.800
the chute.

07:57.800 --> 08:00.060
There you see the horse getting very excited and happy.

08:00.060 --> 08:01.740
This is a good sign.

08:01.740 --> 08:12.920
That means that they're getting more comfortable and more excited and happy about the exercise.

08:12.920 --> 08:18.980
Be sure to be giving the horse breaks depending on their fitness and lots of pats and praise

08:18.980 --> 08:28.580
for simply just engaging with you and having an attempt to listen and learn from you.

08:28.680 --> 08:33.880
Lastly when the horse can be led in and then closely followed then you can send them into

08:33.880 --> 08:38.920
the chute on their own like a large lunge circle.

08:38.920 --> 08:44.480
You can start to almost just lunge them straight into the chute and if they get confused on

08:44.480 --> 08:48.920
direction just gently go back to the lunge position.

08:48.920 --> 08:53.200
You see I just changed my mind and we're going to lunge to the right there.

08:53.200 --> 08:59.540
As your horse gets better at it then you can be more strict and help them with their direction

08:59.540 --> 09:04.620
but understand that for the most part they're just confused on which direction to go and

09:04.620 --> 09:06.060
that's okay.

09:06.060 --> 09:21.100
Just redirect them and you'll be surprised at how much effort they give you.

09:21.100 --> 09:27.100
For the first day that's a perfectly acceptable goal doing two verticals in the chute and

09:27.100 --> 09:29.760
being able to do it all on her own.

09:29.760 --> 09:34.780
This is a great conclusion to her lesson today and she's very happy and rambunctious about

09:34.780 --> 09:35.780
it.

09:35.780 --> 09:45.340
It's a very good sign that she is engaged to work and thinks this is quite a fun game.

09:45.340 --> 09:53.820
As we wind down here you see me offering myself as a steady place to get a pet and she's still

09:53.820 --> 09:57.220
having a little bit of fun and when she's done having her fun she's going to come back

09:57.220 --> 10:01.580
to me and get her pet and that's okay too.

